Simple Node.js Item Management App
Overview

This is a simple Node.js application to manage items. You can view, add, edit, and delete items using a web interface.
How to Run

    Install Node.js:
    Make sure you have Node.js installed on your computer. You can download it from nodejs.org.

    Clone the Repository:
    Clone this repository to your local machine using the following command:

    bash

git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git

Install Dependencies:
Navigate to the project folder and install the required dependencies using:

bash

npm install

Set Up the Database:
Ensure you have a PostgreSQL database running. Update the database configuration in db.js with your connection details.

Run the Application:
Start the application by running:

bash

    npm start

    The app will be accessible at http://localhost:3000.

Features

    View Items:
    Open your web browser and go to http://localhost:3000 to see a list of items.

    Add New Item:
    Click on "Add New Item" to add a new item. Fill in the details and hit "Add Item."

    Edit Item:
    To edit an item, click on "Edit" next to the item you want to modify. Make changes and hit "Update Item."

    Delete Item:
    Click on "Delete" next to an item to remove it from the list.

Known Issues

    If you encounter any problems, feel free to reach out for support.
